# Database & lib helpers

## Source of truth

- Schema, glossary, RLS, sentinels: `docs/Database_Outline.md`
- Migration order & smoke checks: `docs/Setup.md`

## Conventions

- New SQL goes in `sql/greenfield/` with the next numeric prefix (canonical for new projects); never revive or extend `sql/deprecated/`.
- Run migrations **in order** in the Supabase SQL editor (list in `docs/Setup.md`).
- Use locked glossary names (`tools`, `session_categories`, `target_shapes`, `analytics_primary_groups`, …) — no synonym invention.
- Global sentinels use fixed UUIDs + `user_id IS NULL` (see outline + `src/constants/sentinelIds.ts`).
- Templates: jsonb content on session/block/cluster (+ relational exercise). Logs: relational denest/renest in `sessionLogs.ts` (`sql/greenfield/007`).
- RLS: users own their rows; global sentinel rows are readable, not user-writable copies.
- Domain writes go through `src/lib/*Templates.ts`, `sessionLogs.ts`, `taxonomy.ts` — mirror existing list/get/save/delete patterns.
